<TEXT>
jiang qing the ailing widow of the late 
communist chinese leader mao tsetung and a key figure in the 
tumultuous cultural revolution is still in prison and not living 
in a villa an official chinese report said 
the china news service in a dispatch published in hong kong 
newspapers on sunday said a spokesman for the justice ministry had 
denied unconfirmed press reports that the 74yearold jiang was 
released from jail where she is serving a life sentence and lives 
with her daughter in a villa in a beijing suburb 
the justice ministry spokesman said jiang is receiving special 
medical care in jail the china news service reported 
chinese officials said earlier this year that jiang was 
suffering from an unidentified geriatric disease 
recent unconfirmed reports have said she is suffering from 
throat cancer but had refused treatment because it would leave her 
voiceless 
jiang was a member of the notorious gang of four who were 
accused of ordering illegal arrests during the 196676 cultural 
revolution and trying to seize power in china after mao died in 
1976 
members of the gang were convicted in 1981 and jiang was 
sentenced to death but the sentence was commuted to life 
imprisonment in 1983 
</TEXT>
