<TEXT>
puli is a wellbehaved hungarian sheepdog 
that spends most of his time lying in front of a fireplace never 
jumps on the furniture and never makes any noise puli has been 
dead four years 
but his owners suzanne and rob fleming continue to enjoy their 
preserved dog 
its sort of like puli is still alive because of all the 
laughs he gets mrs fleming said 
the flemings once left the fluffy white dog in the back seat of 
their car while they went sailing upon returning they asked a 
friend to let the dog out 
larry kept whistling come here boy took a closer look and 
said uh rob i think you might have left your dog in the car too 
long hes not moving we were in tears we were laughing so 
hard mrs fleming said 
the flemings teenage daughter had a different reaction when 
she learned her parents had decided to have the family pet 
freezedried instead of buried the dog was diagnosed with spinal 
cancer and the flemings had him put to sleep in 1984 
mrs fleming understood her daughters fury i mean how do 
you tell your friends that your parents are having the family dog 
freezedried she asked 
for 650 a taxidermist in portland ore posed the dog lying on 
its side with head up and looking alert the dog weighs about 10 
pounds and needs only occasional cleaning with acetone 
the flemings say they made the right decision and enjoy having 
their dog around the house 
he was like a child to us mrs fleming said 
