<DOCNO> AP880613-0007 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
when the dust storms come kabul 
vanishes from sight behind a white cloud that grittily obscures all 
sense of what is and is not real 
then the winds die down and the dust suspended in the air 
drifts to the ground the sun breaks through and the city of mud 
brick houses and 2 million people shimmers back into view 
its a bit like stepping into a magic spell and visiting 
brigadoon the scottish highlands town in the broadway musical 
that appears for a day once every hundred years before fading away 
into the mist again 
kabul has that same sense 
the distinction between reality and fantasy blurs 
the afghan capital is at once communist and capitalist 
the government of the peoples democratic party of afghanistan 
is one of the soviet unions most successful attempts to impose 
communist rule on a moslem nation 
but here the united states has entered the fray by supporting 
and helping arm the anticommunist guerrillas who are fighting 
afghan and soviet soldiers 
and in spite of the sovietstyle government kabul is a 
capitalist city dollars are avidly sought by merchants who sell 
everything from centuryold handwoven afghan carpets to gaudy lace 
stockings from far east sweatshops 
kabul is a city full of life and increasingly of death 
teenage girls strive for the latest styles as their tailors 
stitch governmentissue blue cotton into school uniforms patterned 
on the skirts and jackets shown in european fashion magazines 
the markets bustle with more traditionally clad women wearing 
the chadri an allenveloping veil that descends in pleats from 
a skullcap with only a coarse mesh panel over the eyes to let the 
wearer see out 
small boys in pajamalike tunics and pants turn cartwheels in 
grassy traffic circles dodging sprays of water from tanker trucks 
that keep the geraniums blossoming 
at night streets are virtually deserted the rare motorist is 
suddenly stopped by an afghan soldier who emerges from the gloom to 
wave his rifle and check the travelers identity 
soviet soldiers have started withdrawing from other cities as 
part of a pullout the kremlin says will by feb 15 end its 
eightyear military intervention but they still surround kabul 
with a ring of tanks armored personnel carriers and fortified 
bunkers 
guerrilla rockets hit kabul several times a week usually at 
night often they land near afghan and soviet military posts but 
rockets are notoriously inaccurate and many of the casualties are 
civilians asleep in their homes 
one of these victims was carried into a hospital xray room a 
few days ago the whitehaired man lay unconscious on a narrow bed 
of ropes woven across a wooden frame his right eye was closed his 
left concealed by a bloody bandage blood stains covered the 
shoulders of his brown tunic and one leg lay at an improbable 
angle under a red plaid blanket 
he had been brought to the hospital bed and all by three men 
wearing turbans baggy trousers and layers of robes 
the old man lived according to a hospital staff member who said 
such victims arrive almost every morning but the staffer refused 
to give specific numbers reflecting a reluctance to make 
statements not authorized by the government 
death is tangible at tapaeshuhadan the hill of the 
martyrs kabuls cemetery for government troops who have died in 
the decade of fighting the mujahedeen or moslem holy warriors 
tapaeshuhadan is offlimits much of the time even to 
mourners for it is in a military zone a visit to the hill quickly 
reveals the reason 
tapaeshuhadan sits atop a huge ammunition dump evident from 
the concrete doorways and little ventilation chimneys built into 
the slopes below the graves 
the members of the peace solidarity and friendship organization 
who escort foreign visitors to the cemtery were at a loss to say 
how many men are buried there but a rough reckoning achieved by 
counting graves in one quadrant and extrapolating made 10000 seem 
a conservative estimate 
these escorted visits add to the blurring of reality and 
unreality in kabul but there are other encounters that seem 
genuine like the one with a man in a crocheted white skullcap who 
declared himself a mujahed one of those seeking to oust the 
government 
he spat on the ground to express his contempt for the afghan 
government communism and the soviet union 
speaking in arabic he said he had learned from the koran 
islams holy book and from three pilgrimmages to mecca in saudi 
arabia one of the countries arming the mujahedeen he said god 
willing the brotherhood of moslems will see victory in 
afghanistan 
</TEXT>
