<TEXT>
the antiimmigration national front has all but 
vanished from the legislature in nationwide elections despite 
winning a stunning 14 percent of the vote in aprils presidential 
balloting 
in national assembly elections two years ago 35 members of the 
farright party won seats on sunday only one survived 
but the front was ambushed less by voters than by a new 
winnertakeall polling system 
not only did party leader jeanmarie le pen lose his seat he 
also dropped 17300 in a bet with a pollster whose organization 
predicted le pen would be defeated 
le pen called the election unfair and undemocratic adding 
that it was unreasonable for a party that won 4 million votes in 
april to be nearly shut out of the legislature in june 
the socialists who won the presidency and took control of the 
national assembly in 1981 made it possible for the national front 
to get into the assembly when they changed the election law from a 
winnertakeall majority system to a proportional one 
the majority system favors large parties the proportional 
system where seats are allotted on the basis of the percentage of 
votes won is better for smaller parties 
when the conservatives ousted the socialists from power in the 
assembly in 1986 they immediately voted back the majority system 
we unfortunately predicted victory of the 
socialistcommunist left even though they are in a minority 
because of the majority system of election which we fought said 
jeanpierre stirbois secretarygeneral of the national front 
the election system was conceived to eliminate the 
national front said le pen and on the whole it achieved its 
objective at least in parliament 
the national front vilified by the other political parties and 
accused of being racist and xenophobic for its antiimmigration 
platform burst onto the political scene in 1984 by winning 11 
percent of the vote in elections for a european parliament 
the party won 98 percent in 1986 legislative elections not 
only entering the assembly for the first time but surpassing 30 
seats the number needed to form a separate parliamentary political 
group 
le pens 144 percent performance in the 1988 presidential 
election was 2 points above the most optimistic prediction 
though suffering a serious setback in this election the 
national front recorded at least one success it brought 
traditional rightist parties into a deal for mutual support in 
several constituencies in recognition of its political strength 
le pen claimed this arrangement allowed the right to blunt what 
otherwise would have been a socialist landslide 
carrying the national front standard will be only yann piat who 
won reelection from a mediterranean district mrs piat the wife 
of a naval officer celebrated both her victory and her 39th 
birthday on sunday 
i am an ardent defender of a strong europe but a fierce 
adversary of uncontrolled immigration she said 
</TEXT>
