<TEXT>
a newly discovered herpes virus may 
cause much of the damage to the immune system in people suffering 
from the deadly disease aids a researcher says 
dr robert gallo one of the discoverers of the aids virus said 
sunday that the herpes virus works in concert with aids to attack 
the white blood cells that orchestrate the bodys defenses against 
disease 
he said the herpes virus can knock out the bodys immune system 
more effectively than acquired immune deficiency syndrome once the 
aids virus has weakened the bodys defense 
the herpes virus appears to be harmless or to produce only very 
mild disease in otherwise normal healthy people gallo said at the 
opening session of the fourth international conference on aids in 
stockholm 
most of us in this room have been exposed to and probably 
infected with this virus while showing little or no sign of it 
he said 
the new herpes virus was discovered by researchers in gallos 
laboratory in 1986 it was initially called hblv for human bcell 
lymphotropic virus and is now referred to as hhv6 human herpes 
virus type six 
this sixth human herpes virus though related is different from 
the herpes viruses that cause cold sores and genital infections 
one of the principal targets of the aids virus is the t4 
lymphocyte a white blood cell that serves as the master 
orchestrator of the bodys immune response to invading organisms 
it appears however that the aids virus only infects a small 
percentage of t4 cells yet it kills a very large percentage of 
them 
there are a number of theories to explain how this might happen 
but gallo proposed that the new herpes virus might be the answer 
in studies in the test tube the herpes virus is a more 
effective killer of t4 cells than is the aids virus gallo said 
it can activate the dormant aids virus and it is more common in 
aids patients and in such highrisk groups as homosexuals and 
drug abusers than it is in the population at large gallo said 
the aids virus weakens the immune system allowing hhv6 to 
enter hhv6 activates the virus and kills cells producing further 
loss of immune defenses and the deadly cycle continues 
to prove that gallo will have to do studies with animals if he 
can find animals that are infected both by the aids virus and 
hhv6 he said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
