flooding triggered by heavy rains in central 
chinas sichuan province killed 11 people and injured 32 over the 
weekend an official chinese news report said 
downpours friday and saturday in sichuans shizhu county sent 
flood waters pouring from local mountains submerging nearly 12500 
acres of crops and ruining two electric stations and 150 homes the 
china news service said in a report appearing today 
the report said the waters quickly receded and services were 
being restored to the affected area 
