affairs as saying that overstaffing costs the state about 162 
billion a year equal to half the total revenue the state receives 
from enterprises each year 
he said many employees spend working hours playing cards or 
watching television at one 800person factory in shijiazhuang 
northeast china employees were found to work only four hours 
during an eighthour shift he said 
china with an urban work force of 120 million has cited low 
productivity and surplus workers as major obstacles to its drive to 
modernize industries and make them more profitable 
but the government is also committed to keeping unemployment at 
the present stated level of 2 percent and has said it must create 
30 million new jobs by 1990 just to keep pace with the expanding 
work force 
factory managers have been given authority to dismiss 
unproductive workers but it is very rare for workers to be fired 
for loafing on the job 
