a subcommittee of the nations largest 
presbyterian body today voted overwhelmingly to recommend adoption 
of a major policy statement on nuclear war 
the revised paper on christian obedience in a nuclear age 
was scheduled to be considered later today by a full committee of 
the 200th general assembly of the presbyterian church usa 
the subcommittee of the committee on peacemaking and 
international relations ended almost four days of attimes 
contentious debate with a 151 vote to recommend adoption of the 
statement 
the subcommittee revised the original proposal to make it clear 
presbyterians considered obedience to government the normal course 
and to soften language that now declares nuclear deterrence 
immoral the subcommittee adopted a writing teams finetuning of 
the policy to agree with earlier changes in recommendations 
