people extradited from foreign countries to 
face criminal charges here cannot avoid defending themselves 
against related civil lawsuits filed in us courts the supreme 
court ruled today 
the justices ruled unanimously against wilfried van 
cauwenberghe a belgian citizen who is trying to avoid having to 
defend himself against a 19 million lawsuit in california 
the court said van cauwenberghe has no right to appeal before 
any trial is held the authority of a los angelesbased federal 
court to preside over the lawsuit 
