van cauwenberghe had been arrested while on a trip to 
switzerland and was extradited to los angeles 
in seeking to have biards civil lawsuit dismissed van 
cauwenberghe argued that the belgian courts are a more convenient 
forum for the civil case and also that extradited individuals are 
immune from such suits 
a federal judge refused to dismiss the suit and the 9th us 
circuit court of appeals said it was premature for it to hear van 
cauwenberghes appeal 
the supreme court today agreed that any such appeal by van 
cauwenberghe can wait until after the trial is completed 
justice thurgood marshall writing for the court said van 
cauwenberghes freedom is not at stake in the case 
van cauwenberghe cannot be imprisoned or required to post bail 
in a civil suit and in fact is not even required to be present at 
the civil trial 
van cauwenberghes right to challenge the outcome of the lawsuit 
can be vindicated after there is a judgment in the suit marshall 
said 
the case is van cauwenberghe vs biard 87336 
