horsford said she has learned that in television you have to 
come out ready with all your lines memorized 
i said im so grateful for every lesson for every showcase 
ive done she said you do a sitcom and you can use everything 
youve learned you dont have time to think of criticism because 
its so fast i think what makes a hit show is an actor giving a 
lot of his or her resource to a writer 
a producer hires you hoping that you can deliver but theres 
no way a producer can anticipate how the audience will respond to 
you the writers pick up little pieces of you and your personality 
and put it into the script an actors heartache is having a great 
line but then losing it because it didnt work in rehearsal in 
television if something doesnt work the first time theres no 
second chance 
when she moved to los angeles two years ago to start work on 
