stalemated talks with japanese officials over beef and orange 
imports in tokyo 
japan has said it will phase out beef import restrictions over a 
threeyear period but needs a 70 percent tariff on us beef to 
keep prices in line with domestic levels us officials want a 
substantially lower tariff 
us negotiators are also expected to urge japan to liberalize 
its citrus market in three years instead of the fiveyear period 
proposed by tokyo 
the margin of error in the poll was not specified 
