<TEXT>
finance ministers of the european economic 
community monday agreed to liberalize the movement of capital 
throughout the 12nation trading bloc 
the new legislation will have to be put into force by eight of 
the 12 member countries by july 1 1990 
spain and ireland have been given until 1992 to implement the 
law greece and portugal have not been assigned a specific 
timetable 
the agreement is a crucial step towards achieving a borderless 
internal market within the eec by the end of 1992 
the legislation will for example allow citizens of one eec 
nation to open a bank account in another eec country it will also 
increase competition among european banks by allowing them to offer 
services throughout the trading bloc 
it should make it possible for european financial 
institutions to catch up with tokyo and new york said jacques 
delors president of the eecs executive commission 
</TEXT>
